This paper presents a machine learning-based method for tuning the parameters of a simulation model to match a real-world model, which is particularly relevant for robotics research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves supervised learning and system identification, which are common topics in machine learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves sim-to-real transfer, which is a common topic in both robotics and machine learning, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper involves predicting rigid body motion, which is a common topic in computer vision, suggesting that cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely but still possible category.
